casebody.data:
Ralph Moss, Individually and as Surviving Executor of Solomon D. Moss, Deceased, Appellant, v. Jacob Cohen and Solomon D. Cohen as Administrator of Fanny Cohen, Deceased, Respondents.

(Submitted May 8, 1899;

decided May 12, 1899.)

Motion to request the Supreme Court to return remittitur and order that plaintiff show cause why it should not be amended, denied, without costs, and without prejudice to the right to renew the motion upon notice. (See 158 N. Y. 240.)
